---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-australians-need', text: 'What Australian Expats Need', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'australia-coverage', text: 'Australia Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'special-considerations', text: 'Special Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Asia Insurance', href: '/best/asia-insurance' },
  { title: 'Worldwide Insurance', href: '/best/worldwide-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Long-Term Insurance', href: '/best/long-term-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'ausNetwork', header: 'Australia Network' },
  { key: 'ausOption', header: 'Australia Coverage' },
  { key: 'apacCoverage', header: 'Asia-Pacific' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', ausNetwork: 'Excellent', ausOption: 'Optional', apacCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Australian returnees' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', ausNetwork: 'Good', ausOption: 'Optional', apacCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Global + Australia' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', ausNetwork: 'Good', ausOption: 'Optional', apacCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'Europe-based Aussies' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', ausNetwork: 'Moderate', ausOption: 'Optional', apacCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'US-connected Aussies' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', ausNetwork: 'Moderate', ausOption: 'Optional', apacCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'Budget option' },
];

const considerationsColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'importance', header: 'Why It Matters' },
  { key: 'recommendation', header: 'Recommendation' },
];

const considerationsRows = [
  { factor: 'Medicare eligibility', importance: 'May lose Medicare abroad', recommendation: 'Verify status' },
  { factor: 'Australia return visits', importance: 'Family visits, potential return', recommendation: 'Include Australia option' },
  { factor: 'Asia-Pacific focus', importance: 'Many Aussies live in APAC', recommendation: 'Ensure APAC coverage' },
  { factor: 'Reciprocal agreements', importance: 'Some countries have Medicare agreements', recommendation: 'Understand limits' },
  { factor: 'Private health rebate', importance: 'Tax implications of private insurance', recommendation: 'Consult advisor' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Insurance for Australian Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Australian expats. Find plans with Australia coverage options, strong Asia-Pacific networks, and benefits for Aussies abroad."
  headline="Best Insurance for Australian Expats"
  subheadline="Australian expats have unique needs—Medicare considerations, Asia-Pacific coverage, and options for returning home. Here are the best insurance options for Aussies abroad."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-australian-expat-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Australian Expats</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best options for Australians abroad:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🦘</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Australians</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong Australian presence through Bupa Australia, excellent APAC network, familiar service.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌏</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Global + APAC</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Excellent worldwide coverage with strong Asia-Pacific presence and Australia options.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Europe</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Good for Australians living in Europe with Australia return options.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💡</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Key Consideration</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Medicare Rules</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Living abroad affects Medicare eligibility. International insurance is essential.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-australians-need">What Australian Expats Need</h2>
  <p>
    Australians living abroad have specific insurance considerations:
  </p>

  <h3>Medicare Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Medicare based on Australian residency</li>
    <li>Living abroad may affect eligibility</li>
    <li>Reciprocal health agreements with some countries</li>
    <li>Not all care covered under agreements</li>
    <li>International insurance fills the gaps</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Asia-Pacific Focus</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Many Australians live in Southeast Asia</li>
    <li>Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand popular</li>
    <li>Strong APAC coverage important</li>
    <li>Quality varies by country</li>
    <li>Regional hospitals need coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Australia Return Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Visits to family in Australia</li>
    <li>Access to Australian healthcare</li>
    <li>Potential permanent return</li>
    <li>Bridge Medicare gaps</li>
    <li>Private hospital options</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Coverage for Australian Expats"
    description="Compare plans with Australia and global coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Australian Expat Plan Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best for Australians</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is the natural choice for Australian expats.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong Australian connection (Bupa Australia)</li>
    <li>Excellent Australia coverage options</li>
    <li>Strong Asia-Pacific network</li>
    <li>Familiar to Australians</li>
    <li>Global coverage worldwide</li>
    <li>Premium service quality</li>
    <li>Good private hospital network</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Best for those wanting quality coverage with Australian ties. Worth it for comprehensive protection.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Global + APAC</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers excellent options for Australian expats.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong global coverage</li>
    <li>Excellent Asia-Pacific presence</li>
    <li>Australia coverage options</li>
    <li>Modular flexibility</li>
    <li>1.5M+ providers globally</li>
    <li>24/7 global support</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Australia adds to premium. Good balance of global and Australian coverage. Excellent for APAC-based Aussies.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Allianz Care — Best for Europe</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care works well for Australians in Europe.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excellent European coverage</li>
    <li>Australia options available</li>
    <li>Good global network</li>
    <li>Multilingual support</li>
    <li>Competitive European pricing</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best for Europe-based Aussies. Australia coverage as add-on. Good for working holiday makers in Europe.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our full Allianz Care review</a></p>

  <h2 id="australia-coverage">Australia Coverage Options</h2>

  <h3>Full Australia Inclusion</h3>
  <p>
    Complete Australia coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Private healthcare in Australia covered</li>
    <li>Access to private hospitals</li>
    <li>Not reliant on Medicare</li>
    <li>Skip public waiting lists</li>
    <li>Adds to premium cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Australia for Visits Only</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage during return trips:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Emergency and necessary care covered</li>
    <li>Time-limited (e.g., 90 days/year)</li>
    <li>Good for family visits</li>
    <li>Lower premium impact</li>
    <li>May combine with Medicare for some care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Asia-Pacific Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Regional focus:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strong coverage throughout APAC</li>
    <li>Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand networks</li>
    <li>Japan, South Korea coverage</li>
    <li>Good for regional living</li>
    <li>Often includes Australia option</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Your Australian Connection"
    description="Find the right level of Australia coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="special-considerations">Special Considerations for Australian Expats</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={considerationsColumns} rows={considerationsRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Medicare Eligibility</h3>
  <p>
    Understanding Medicare rules:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Medicare for Australian residents</li>
    <li>Living abroad long-term may affect status</li>
    <li>Can maintain Medicare with proper documentation</li>
    <li>Reciprocal agreements with some countries</li>
    <li>Check your specific situation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Reciprocal Health Agreements</h3>
  <p>
    Countries with agreements:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>UK, Ireland, New Zealand</li>
    <li>Netherlands, Belgium, Finland, Italy, Malta</li>
    <li>Norway, Sweden, Slovenia</li>
    <li>Limited coverage—not comprehensive</li>
    <li>Private insurance still recommended</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Returning to Australia</h3>
  <p>
    Planning potential return:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Medicare typically available upon return</li>
    <li>May need to re-establish residency</li>
    <li>Private insurance for immediate coverage</li>
    <li>Maintain Australia option in plan</li>
    <li>Easier transition with continuous coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Private Health Insurance Rebate</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Australian tax rebate for private insurance</li>
    <li>May not apply while living abroad</li>
    <li>International insurance usually not eligible</li>
    <li>Consult tax advisor for your situation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I lose Medicare when I move abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Not necessarily. Medicare eligibility depends on Australian residency, not physical presence. You may maintain Medicare if you're still considered an Australian resident. Check with Services Australia for your specific situation.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use Medicare when visiting Australia?</h3>
  <p>
    If you've maintained Medicare eligibility, yes. If you've lost eligibility, you may face charges. Reciprocal agreements exist for citizens of certain countries. Private international insurance provides certainty.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for Australian expats?</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is the natural choice given their strong Australian presence through Bupa Australia. They understand Australian expats and have excellent APAC coverage. Cigna Global is also excellent for global coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Do reciprocal health agreements provide enough coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    No. Reciprocal agreements provide basic public healthcare, not comprehensive coverage. They don't cover all treatments, private care, or repatriation. Private international insurance is recommended.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I include Australia in my coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes. Most Australian expats visit family, may need Australian specialists, or might return. Australia coverage provides peace of mind and access to private care during visits.
  </p>

  <h3>What about coverage in Southeast Asia?</h3>
  <p>
    Many major insurers have excellent Southeast Asian networks. Singapore, Thailand, and Malaysia have world-class private hospitals. Verify coverage quality in your specific location with your insurer.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Medicare rules and eligibility vary. We are not insurance brokers or legal advisors. Verify current rules and coverage directly.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
